result.execSummary:
The defendant Ukeitha U Willaby was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • 1st-Degree Recklessly Endangering Safety [Modifiers: Use of a Dangerous Weapon, Domestic Abuse Incident], a class F felony, Wisconsin Statutes 941.30(1).
  • 1st-Degree Recklessly Endangering Safety [Modifiers: Use of a Dangerous Weapon], a class F felony, Wisconsin Statutes 941.30(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Ukeitha U Willaby in court with attorney Scott Franklin Anderson.  Defendant Ukeitha U Willaby in custody.  Owen Piotrowski appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Sentencing proceeded. PSI reviewed. Corrections and additions were made. Court found the state has satisfied victims' rights law. Statements by parties and defendant. 
AS TO COUNT 1:
The court sentenced the defendant to a MAXIMUM term in the Wisconsin State Prison of 12 years, consecutive to count 2, credit for 495 days time served, the term of INITIAL CONFINEMENT is 8 years, the term of EXTENDED SUPERVISION is 4 years. 
AS TO COUNT 2:
The court sentenced the defendant to a MAXIMUM term in the Wisconsin State Prison of 10 years, consecutive, credit for zero days time served, the term of INITIAL CONFINEMENT is 6 years, the term of EXTENDED SUPERVISION is 4 years.
CONDITIONS OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION
Mental health evaluation, take all prescribed medications.
AODA assessment, comply with recommended treatment.
Absolute sobriety.
Treatment and/or counseling as determined by agent.
No contact with victims
Obtain/maintain employment.
Obtain GED/HSED.
No contact with firearms.
Pay all MANDATORY court costs, fees, and surcharges including: DNA & DV surcharges to be paid from 25% of prison funds, balance paid during Extended Supervision, failure to pay results in a civil judgment.
Provide DNA Sample.
Court finds defendant is NOT eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program OR the Wisconsin Substance Abuse Program.
Court advised defendant of right to seek post conviction relief.
Court advised due to felony conviction the defendant is prohibited from firearm possession, and defendant's voting rights are suspended and may not vote until civil rights are restored.
Filed: Pretrial Sentence Credit, Notice of Right to Seek Post-Conviction Relief, Ineligible Voting Notice & Acknowledgement, Written Explanation of Determinate Sentence.
